{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"**Topology Summary**\n\nUse a standard static CMOS inverter powered from a 5 V rail. `Vout` is the shared drain/output node between the pull-up PMOS and pull-down NMOS. `Vin` drives both transistor gates directly.\n\nWhen `Vin = 0 V`, PMOS is on and NMOS is off, so `Vout` is pulled to `VDD`. When `Vin = 5 V`, NMOS is on and PMOS is off, so `Vout` is pulled to ground.\n\n**Device/Function List**\n\n- `VDD` supply: independent DC voltage source from node `VDD` to `0`, value `5 V`.\n- Input source `Vin`: independent voltage source from node `Vin` to `0`, used as the `.dc` sweep source.\n- NMOS pull-down:\n  - Drain: `Vout`\n  - Gate: `Vin`\n  - Source: `0`\n  - Bulk: `0`\n  - Model: `NMOS`, threshold about `0.7 V`\n- PMOS pull-up:\n  - Source: `VDD`\n  - Gate: `Vin`\n  - Drain: `Vout`\n  - Bulk: `VDD`\n  - Model: `PMOS`, threshold about `-0.7 V`\n\n**Bias/Reference Strategy**\n\n`VDD` is fixed at `5 V` relative to ground node `0`. `Vin` is explicitly driven by its own independent voltage source and swept from `0 V` to `5 V`. Bulk terminals should be tied to their respective sources to avoid body-effect surprises in this simple inverter.\n\n**Signal Or Feedback Path**\n\nThere is no feedback path. This is a direct combinational inverter: `Vin` controls both gates, and `Vout` is formed by the complementary pull-up/pull-down conduction path between `VDD` and `0`.\n\n**SPICE/Netlist Constraints**\n\n- Final file must be named `p7.cir`.\n- Preserve node names exactly: `Vin`, `Vout`.\n- Use exactly one NMOS and one PMOS transistor.\n- Include an independent DC input source named `Vin` so `.dc Vin 0 5 0.1` sweeps the source correctly.\n- Include primitive MOS models with thresholds:\n  - `NMOS` with `VTO = 0.7`\n  - `PMOS` with `VTO = -0.7`\n- Use primitive MOSFET devices only; no behavioral inverter or controlled-source shortcut.\n\n**Failure Risks To Avoid**\n\n- Do not leave `Vin` floating; it must be driven by an independent source named `Vin`.\n- Do not accidentally make `Vin` only a node name while the voltage source has another name, because `.dc Vin ...` must reference the source name.\n- Do not swap PMOS source/bulk away from `VDD`; PMOS source and bulk should both connect to `VDD`.\n- Do not swap NMOS source/bulk away from ground; NMOS source and bulk should both connect to `0`.\n- Do not use extra transistors, resistive loads, behavioral sources, or logic primitives.\n- Ensure `Vout` is only the shared output node between the PMOS drain and NMOS drain, not tied directly to `VDD` or ground."}}
